WHY GPL-2.0
-----------
The flashable image in `image/` bundles GPL-2.0 software — the Linux 4.9
kernel, BusyBox, and a Buildroot-built userspace — so distribution of this
repository is governed by the GPL-2.0. Our own scripts and project overlay
are released under the same terms.

ATTRIBUTION / UPSTREAMS
----------------------
- OS base (kernel + rootfs): frederic/superbird-buildroot — Buildroot,
  GPL-2.0-or-later. https://github.com/frederic/superbird-buildroot
- Flasher (`tools/_flasher.py`, `image/manual/superbird_device.py`):
  adapted from the bishopdynamics/superbird-tool line; see that upstream
  for its own terms. https://github.com/bishopdynamics/superbird-tool
- Low-level USB Burn Mode work: frederic/superbird-bulkcmd,
  frederic/amlogic-usbdl.
- SoC platform: Amlogic G12A BSP.
- Bootloader: stock Spotify/Amlogic — NOT modified and NOT redistributed
  here (it already lives on the device's eMMC boot partitions).

SOURCE FOR GPL COMPONENTS
-------------------------
Corresponding source for the GPL components shipped in `image/` is available
through the upstream Buildroot project (frederic/superbird-buildroot) and the
respective package upstreams. The project overlay sources are in `source/`.
